description: This file implements placeholder stubs for an LPC Connector Object in C, designed for use within the Advanced Networking Service Container (ANSC). It includes functions for dispatching calls, freeing output buffers, and handling events, but the implementations are minimal, returning default or error status.

methods.name: ANSC_STATUS AnscLpccoCpcCallDispatch(ANSC_HANDLE hThisObject,ANSC_HANDLE hLpcPartyAddr,void * pInputBuffer,ULONG ulInputSize,void ** ppOutputBuffer,PULONG pulOutputSize,PULONG pulErrorCode)
methods.description: Dispatches an IMCP-based SLAP call via LPC, currently a stub returning an internal error.

methods.name: ANSC_STATUS AnscLpccoCpcFreeOutputBuffer(ANSC_HANDLE hThisObject,void * pOutputBuffer)
methods.description: Releases the output buffer for LPC calls, currently a stub returning 'unapplicable'.

methods.name: ANSC_STATUS AnscLpccoCpcNotifyEvent(ANSC_HANDLE hThisObject,ULONG ulEvent,ANSC_HANDLE hReserved)
methods.description: Notifies LPC events, currently a stub returning 'unapplicable'.
